  <description type="morphology">Aerial flowering stems 1–1.5(–2) dm, bractless or with 1 leaflike bract ca. midlength. Leaf blades usually linear-oblanceolate, 1.5–3 × 0.2–0.5 cm, densely lanate to tomentose on both surfaces. Involucres usually campanulate; tubes 3–4.5 mm; teeth 2.5–3.5 mm. Flowers (5–)6–9 mm; perianth cream or ochroleucous.</description>
